HEADWORD: Bullary
<hw>Bul"la*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bullarium</ets>: cf. F. <ets>bullairie</ets>. See <er>Bull</er> an
edict.]</ety> <def>A collection of papal bulls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bullary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bullary
<hw>Bul"la*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Bullaries</plw> <pr>(-r⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Boilary</er>.]</ety> <def>A place for boiling or preparing salt; a
boilery.</def> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And certain salt fats or <qex>bullaries</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bills
in Chancery.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bullate</ent>⟦br⟧
